-- Korean Air Lines to Operate Its First Airbus A380 Superjumbo in May 2011
-- B y   S o o k y u n g   S e o
-- 2010-12-28T00:35:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-28/korean-air-lines-to-operate-its-first-airbus-a380-superjumbo-in-may-2011.html
Korean Air Lines Co. will begin
flying its first Airbus SAS A380 superjumbo in May.  The plane will be fitted with 407 seats, including 12 in
first class and 94 in business class, according to an e-mailed
statement from the carrier today. The upper deck of the plane
will be exclusively business class.  The airline will receive a total of five A380s by the end
of next year. It will then get another five from 2012 to 2014,
the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sookyung Seo in Seoul at 
 sseo10@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
